    Enhanced SortUtil class
    There are 2 selectionSort methods one that takes an int and one that takes a type called T which is really a type that implements Comparable.

    Both methods will NOT return a value NOTE: All passed parameters are always final!

      • selectionSort

        public static <T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>> void selectionSort(T[] array)
        The selectSort method sorts the array in ascending order. The array is of type T which is ultimately of type Comparable. This method has been rewritten to remove the raw Comparable and replace it with the specific type being passed in using the generic. This mean the appropriate compareTo method is called.
        Type Parameters:
        T - This describes a generic type
        Parameters:
        array - The array to be sorted
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the Comparable [] array is null or if the array length < 1
